–1139":"1080–1139","1085–Female":"1085–preminula","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1060–1135":"1060–1135.","1065–1105":"1065–1105.","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1105":"1105.","um 1110":"oko 1110.","1135":"1135.","18. April 1139":"18. travnja 1139.","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1085":"1085","um 1080":"oko 1080.","1171":"1171","1060":"1060","Limburg, Belgien":"Limburg, Belgija","Borgloon, Limburg, Belgium":"Borgloon, Limburg, Belgija","Bayern, Deutschland":"Bayern, Njemačka"},"cs":{"um 1080–18. April 1139":"okolo 1080–18. dubna 1139","1080–1139":"1080–1139","1085–Female":"1085–Zesnulá","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1060–1135":"1060–1135","1065–1105":"1065–1105","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1105":"1105","um 1110":"okolo 1110","1135":"1135","18. April 1139":"18. dubna 1139","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1085":"1085","um 1080":"okolo 1080","1171":"1171","1060":"1060","Limburg, Belgien":"Limburg, Belgie","Borgloon, Limburg, Belgium":"Borgloon, Limburg, Belgie","Bayern, Deutschland":"Bavorsko, Německo"},"da":{"um 1080–18. April 1139":"omkring 1080–18. april 1139","1080–1139":"1080–1139","1085–Female":"1085–Afdød","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1060–1135":"1060–1135","1065–1105":"1065–1105","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1105":"1105","um 1110":"omkring 1110","1135":"1135","18. April 1139":"18. april 1139","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1085":"1085","um 1080":"omkring 1080","1171":"1171","1060":"1060","Limburg, Belgien":"Limburg, Belgien","Borgloon, Limburg, Belgium":"Borgloon, Limburg, Belgien","Bayern, Deutschland":"Bayern, Tyskland"},"nl":{"um 1080–18. April 1139":"circa 1080–18 april 1139","1080–1139":"1080–1139","1085–Female":"1085–Overleden","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1060–1135":"1060–1135","1065–1105":"1065–1105","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1105":"1105","um 1110":"circa 1110","1135":"1135","18. April 1139":"18 april 1139","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1085":"1085","um 1080":"circa 1080","1171":"1171","1060":"1060","Limburg, Belgien":"Limburg, België","Borgloon, Limburg, Belgium":"Borgloon, Limburg, België","Bayern, Deutschland":"Bayern, Duitsland"},"en":{"um 1080–18. April 1139":"about 1080–18 April 1139","1080–1139":"1080–1139","1085–Female":"1085–Deceased","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1060–1135":"1060–1135","1065–1105":"1065–1105","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1105":"1105","um 1110":"about 1110","1135":"1135","18. April 1139":"18 April 1139","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1085":"1085","um 1080":"about 1080","1171":"1171","1060":"1060","Limburg, Belgien":"Limburg, Belgium","Borgloon, Limburg, Belgium":"Borgloon, Limburg, Belgium","Bayern, Deutschland":"Bavaria, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"van","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Anh, Thanh, Hung, Minh, Vinh, Dung, Hue, Huong, Lan, Quang, Tan, Thuy, Hong, Chi, Hang, Ho, Pok, Sang, Bai, Chin, Ching, Chu, Chuan, Dong.","Vietnamese (<b>Vạn</b>): from the Chinese surname 萬, see   Wan   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Văn</b>): from the Chinese surnames 文 or 聞, see   Wen   2 and 3, and also 5 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Wan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Yi, Qi, Qiang, Wai, Yiu, Yuk, Chien-Min, Fang, Hin, Jichun, Li, Man, Chung, Min, Yiping, Pak, Sik, Sung Man.  Vietnamese Tin, Bang, Da, Hien, Hoi, Lan, Minh Quang, Sau, Tich, Tung, Yaping, Yuet.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 萬, which means ‘ten thousand’ literally or ‘very great number’ figuratively: (i) from the personal name of Bi Wan (畢萬), an official in the state of Jin (located in present-day Shanxi province). He was said to be a descendant of Bi Gong Gao (known as Duke of Bi), the 15th son of the virtuous King Wen of Zhou (reined 1152–1056  BC ). Bi Wan was later granted the fiefdom of Wei (魏), which in 403  BC  became the state of Wei (located in present-day Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces). Some of his descendants adopted Wei (魏) as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his personal name, as their surname. (ii) from the personal name Wan (萬), style name of Rui Bo (芮伯, the Earl of Rui), an official of the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ), who was granted the fief Rui (located in Ruicheng in Shaanxi province). Some of his descendants inherited Rui (芮), the name of the fief, as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his style name, as their surname. (iii) from the placename Wan (萬), the name of a fief (located in Juxian in Shandong province) granted during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ) to an official in the ancient state of Chu. (iv) from the first element of the name of the Wan Si (萬俟) family, who lived in the downstream areas of the Yellow River during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD ). (v) from the second element of the name of the Tu Wan (吐萬) family, who are members of the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 完, meaning ‘complete’ in Chinese: (i) said to be borne by the descendants of Huan Zhui, a grandson of the Duke Huan of Song (ruler of the state of Song, died 651  BC ). (ii) from Wan (完), the name of Qu Wan (屈完), an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn Period (770–476  BC ). (iii) shortened form of the compound surname Wan-Yan (完顔), a surname from minority ethnic groups such as Juchen ethnic group in ancient northern China."]}]},{"name":"Loon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","variant of <b>Lond</b>, from Middle English <i>launde</i> ‘glade’, or from one of the placenames derived from it such as <i>Laund</i> (of which there are examples in Yorkshire, Lancashire, and Leicestershire), or from the abbey of this name in Leicestershire. Compare   Lon  .","possibly a variant of English   Lund  , which is either a topographic name from Old Norse <i>lundr</i> ‘grove’, or a habitational name from a place called with this word."],"variants":[{"name":"Lon","meanings":["English: probably a variant of <b>Lond</b>, from Middle English <i>launde</i> ‘glade’, or from one of the placenames derived from it such as <i>Laund</i> (of which there are examples in Yorkshire, Lancashire, and Leicestershire), or from the abbey of this name in Leicestershire. Compare   Lown  .","Cambodian: written លន់, corresponding to the Khmer word meaning e.g. ‘(to be) superb’. Compare   Lun   4.","Burmese (Shan): from a personal name usually forming part of a compound name, of unexplained etymology. Compare   Lone   4. — Note: Since Shans do not have hereditary surnames, this name was registered as such only after immigration of its bearers to the US."]},{"name":"Lowndes","meanings":["English: variant of   Lown  ."]},{"name":"Lownes","meanings":["English: variant of   Lown  ."]},{"name":"Lundy","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: habitational name from any of several places called Lundie, for example one near Doune in Perthshire.","Irish: topographic name from Anglo-Norman French <i>de la Launde</i> ‘of the glade’. Compare   Lown   1.","Americanized form of Norwegian   Lunde  ."]}]},{"name":"Arnold","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  Jewish: Yiddish contracted form of   Aaron .","2  English: short form of   Arnold ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Arnold II van Loon was born about 1080, in Bavaria, Germany, his father, Arnold I graaf van Loon, was 22 and his mother, Agnes von Mainz-Rieneck, was 16. He married Adelheid about 1110. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 18 April 1139, in Limburg, Belgium, at the age of 60."},"et":{"um 1080–18. April 1139":"umbes 1080–18. aprill 1139","1080–1139":"1080–1139","1085–Female":"1085–Surnud","1110–1171":"1110–1171","1060–1135":"1060–1135","1065–1105":"1065–11